<br>
Total: 40 Cards, not including magi  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"> Kazm has one main goal, and that is to stall and get as many cards as possible to set up Bria. If you can, go first and play ONLY the Giant Baldar, or, if you got a good draw, a Rock Hyren. When your opponent goes, they must play creatures, which will more often than not, feed Kazm. When Giant Baldar falls to six energy, start playing more creatures, such as Kazm&#39;s other starter,<br>
Baldar, so he can Smash the smaller opposition. Kazm does have the ability to win the game by himself, so don&#39;t commit suicide just because you have everything you need for Bria. <br>
<br>
When Kazm falls, you should have these cards (at least): Rock Hyren, Staff of Keepers, and a few Jagged Rocks. When you reveal Bria, chose Cald as your region and grab the Lense and Armor. Play the Staff, the Armor, and the Lense, then go ahead and blow up whatever evil card the opposition may have. Play the Hyren, or, preferably, Boots it. Keep the Hyren pumped up with Jagged Rocks, and play more creatures if you can.<br>
<br>
If you&#39;re wondering, there IS a reason for having Stalkers and BOL. That reason is because some situations call for dropping a free Stalker if you don&#39;t have energy for Beam. Protect your Cald relics with the Mirrors, and cast cheaper spells with the Robes.<br>
<br>
Targ&#39;n is just clean-up. You shouldn&#39;t have to use him, but if you do, just beat the opponent down with your Enhanced Invulnerability. If he happens to draw the Cald relic, just turn them into Tomorrow&#39;s Jewel fodder. Enjoy! ;) </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
